> About 1 hour before you're ready to cook, remove prime rib from packaging; place
> on a baking sheet (larger side down) and bring to room temperature. Bring
> @garlic herb butter{2%tablespoon} to room temperature.

> If cheesecakes are frozen, thaw at room temperature for ~{2-3%hours} before
> serving.

== Prime Rib ==

Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat #oven{} to 275 degrees.

Tent @prime rib{1} loosely with #foil{}. Roast on middle rack until cooked to
desired doneness, about ~{1.5%hours}. Transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest,
covered, at least ~{30%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{4%tablespoon} and
@creamy horseradish sauce{3%ounce}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

== Carrots, Asparagus & Potatoes ==

While prime rib rests, increase oven temperature to 425 degrees. Wash and dry
produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces.
Trim and discard woody bottom ends from @asparagus{18%ounce}. Quarter
@lemon{1}. Cut @potatoes{16%ounce} into ½-inch pieces.

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{4%teaspoon},
@maple syrup{2.5%ounce}, salt, @cinnamon{1%teaspoon}, and pepper. Roast on top
rack until tender and slightly caramelized, ~{20-25%minutes}. Toss asparagus and
lemon wedges on a second baking sheet with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper.
Roast on middle rack until tender and lightly browned, ~{10-12%minutes}. Carefully
squeeze roasted lemon wedges over asparagus; toss with garlic herb butter until
melted and combined.

Place potatoes in a #large pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches.
Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup potato
cooking liquid, then drain. Return potatoes to pot; mash with
@black truffle butter{1%ounce} until smooth, adding splashes of reserved potato
cooking liquid as needed. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Keep covered
off heat until ready to serve.

== Rolls ==

If desired, once asparagus is done, place @Parker House rolls{8%piece} on a
third baking sheet. Bake rolls on middle rack until warmed through,
~{4-6%minutes}.

Once prime rib has rested, halve lengthwise, then slice against the grain into
½-inch-thick pieces. Serve with creamy horseradish sauce on the side for dipping.

== Optional Sides and Accompaniments ==

@flatbreads{2%piece} can be warmed to serve alongside.

{@dried cranberries{1%ounce}, @cashews{0.5%ounce}, and @cranberry jam{1}} make
great toppings for appetizers.

@ricotta cheese{4%ounce}, @Granny Smith apple{1}(sliced), @Grand Cru cheese{12%ounce},
and @antipasto gran beretta{6%ounce} can be served for a cheese board.

Fresh @?orange{} slices add color and brightness to your presentation.

@White chocolate raspberry swirl cheesecakes{6%unit} make the perfect ready-to-eat
dessert to cap off this meal.